1. Ensure your oven is empty. Remove the oven racks,
broiler pan, cookware and bakeware, all cooking utensils
and aluminum foil and, on some models, the temperature
probe from the oven.

2. Use a damp cloth to clean inside door edge and the 1½"
(38 mm) area around the inside oven cavity frame, being
certain not to move or bend the gasket.

3. Wipe out any loose soil to reduce smoke and avoid
damage. At high temperatures, foods react with porcelain.
Staining, etching, pitting, or faint white spots can result.
This will not affect cooking performance.
